[normal]DFID and the rights of people with disabilities 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]15. The UK government should also ensure that its own domestic laws are in compliance with the CRPD and all other human rights laws ratified by the UK relevant to persons with disabilities. This includes, in particular, l
[normal]aws governing legal capacity. At the same time the UK could consider sharing its decades of experience of implementing disability discrimination legislation, for example.
